About this item

Product details

From trails in the woods to the first day of class, the Ozark Trail 25 Ltr Hiker Pack is designed to keep you prepared for all sorts of adventures. A roomy main compartment provides plenty of space for books, electronics and more. The shoulder straps and adjustments make for a comfortable carry even while fully loaded. Designed for work, school or play, it helps carry the essentials with ease, so you can get through your everyday adventures. This backpack is suitable to be used by a senior, adult, teen and kids. The three year warranty ensures this backpack will fit your lifestyle for many years to come.

Directions

Fabric Care Instructions

Cleaning as needed: Using a mild soap and a damp sponge, wipe out the inside and outside of the bag. Be sure to completely air dry the pack with the zippers open prior to storing. Stubborn stains may require scrubbing with a soft bristle nylon brush. However, please note that excessive cleaning may damage the protective fabric coatings and is NOT RECOMMENDED. Never put your pack in the washer or dryer. Heat will damage the protective fabric coatings.

Our warranties do not include coverage for personal belongings that have been stored in any of our packs or accessories. Other incidental and consequential losses are excluded. Excellent Small Backpack for Storage and Day Trips

This is an excellent value for the cost. I use these small backpacks as mobile fishing tackle kits, gun/shooting supply kits for range/hunting days and I also use them to pack supplies on hikes in the country and the city. For $11 this is an exceptional little backpack. Most modern backpacks are HUGE. This backpack is small and fits most of the supplies I need for a day out. Well made - I have one that I have been using for kayak fishing for about seven years and it is still in excellent shape. There are enough compartments to keep supplies segregated and organized. Also, easy to access. Over the years I have bought four of these packs - three for myself and one for a friend to put his fishing supplies in for kayak trips.
